We do not "gain" consciousness here. We enter as fully conscious beings. We are not here to pay some ancient ancestral debt (though if you like the language: We are here to complete our ancestral mission - for you family, your community & global (for all humanity) ancestors). Nor born in debt to some overlord, divine or not.
We are here because we were "trained" to be here. From a higher or larger i.e. more encompassing viewpoint, this is where we "chose/were chosen" to be.

div.div:
Inherent (actual or imagined) or inherited fears. When once these behaviours have become embedded in the societial systems (systemic), the can then be consciously manipulated by those who have some percieved gain from said manipulations.
Eg: Salesman, news reporters, artists, etc.
Who has more to gain than those who hold power and wealth: "Everything to gain, everything to lose" is the refrain of kings and CEO's.
A billionaire loses a billion, and has to live in his mansion on a measly million or so a year, having to trade or sell his other 5 abodes, perhaps let go of his luxury cars. Joe lost his business, had debts to pay, loses his house. Now has no money, no house, no job and little prospect of ever attaining a decent life. And we say that the billionaire lost everything? Because it is bigger, higher, faster, does not mean it is better!
